<subSubSection id="40A284DDFFB7FFB2FF62FBE1FC0B3306" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0807D756FFB7FFB2FF62FBE1FD9932D9" blockId="3.[148,977,977,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FF62FBE1FE79325C" bold="true" box="[172,446,1083,1104]" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Distribution and Diversity.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FE0AFBE1FDE9325C" box="[452,558,1083,1104]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FDF6FBE1FD59325C" box="[568,670,1083,1104]" name="Venezuela" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FD66FBE1FD30325C" box="[680,759,1083,1104]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FCEBFBE1FCA9325C" box="[805,878,1083,1104]" name="Bolivia" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. There are five known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FE16FB8CFDEF3267" box="[472,552,1110,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Melchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FE16FB8CFDEF3267" box="[472,552,1110,1131]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Melchus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, four of which are described herein. These new species are 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FE8CFBABFDD23289" authority="Anderson" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[322,533,1136,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Melchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gomezi">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FE8CFBABFE6B328A" box="[322,428,1137,1158]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">M. gomezi</emphasis>
Anderson
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FD92FBAAFD0A3289" box="[604,717,1136,1157]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FD13FBABFC513289" authority="Anderson" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[733,918,1136,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Melchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jolyi">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FD13FBABFCEA328A" box="[733,813,1137,1158]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">M. jolyi</emphasis>
Anderson
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FF5AFB51FF3D32AC" box="[148,250,1163,1184]" name="Venezuela" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FEC5FB51FE3032AC" authority="Anderson" authorityName="Anderson" box="[267,503,1163,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Melchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FEC5FB51FE4A32AC" box="[267,397,1163,1184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">M. perplexus</emphasis>
Anderson
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FDF1FB51FD4032AC" box="[575,647,1163,1184]" name="Bolivia" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FD09FB51FC5232AC" authority="Anderson" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2003" box="[711,917,1163,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Melchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onorei">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FD09FB51FCEB32AC" box="[711,812,1163,1184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">M. onorei</emphasis>
Anderson
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="70AF97C6FFB7FFB2FF5AFB7CFF2132B7" box="[148,230,1190,1211]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. The remaining species is 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FE2CFB7CFD0532B7" authority="Lacordaire" authorityName="Lacordaire" box="[482,706,1190,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Melchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leprosus">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FE2CFB7CFD9532B7" box="[482,594,1190,1211]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">M. leprosus</emphasis>
Lacordaire
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FD02FB7CFC7D32B7" authority="Lacordaire" authorityName="Lacordaire" box="[716,954,1190,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Daisya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbratilis">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FD02FB7CFC8A32B7" box="[716,845,1190,1211]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">M. umbratilis</emphasis>
Lacordaire
</taxonomicName>
is transferred to the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="CFB8ACD5FFB7FFB2FE61FB1AFD9932D9" authority="Anderson." authorityName="Anderson." box="[431,606,1216,1237]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Daisya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FE61FB1AFE3532D9" box="[431,498,1216,1237]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Daisya</emphasis>
Anderson.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0807D756FFB7FFB2FF62FB00FC0B3306" blockId="3.[148,977,977,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis id="3ACC0B44FFB7FFB2FF62FB00FE9C32E3" bold="true" box="[172,347,1242,1263]" pageId="3" pageNumber="416">Natural History.</emphasis>
Adult specimens have been collected in mid-elevation moist tropical forest. No other information is available on the natural history of this genus.
</paragraph>
